						               													<description>The Take is about crooked cops taking money. It is played over the course of several rounds. Each round, each player takes a bill(card) worth between 1 and 5 thousand dollars. In the second half of the game each player gets an opportunity to take an action after all players have taken their money for the round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are three ways to win the game:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    If the deck of cards runs out, the player with the most money wins at the end of the final round.&amp;#10;    If a player correctly accuses a player of having the most money,the accuser immediately wins.&amp;#10;    If a player correctly accuses another player of having the least money, the player with the most money wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are 4 basic actions that players can take by spending money from their hand.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Stakeout: Adjust turn order.&amp;#10;    Audit: Look at another player's cards.&amp;#10;    Accuse: Accuse a player of having the most or least money.&amp;#10;    Defame: Block a player from taking an action.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
